---
// PrivacyPage.astro — Privacy Policy page
---

<div class="privacy">
  <div class="privacy__inner">
    <h1 class="privacy__title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <hr class="privacy__divider" />
    <p class="privacy__date">Last Updated: Nov 12, 2025</p>

    <section class="privacy__section">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>Welcome to the website and products operated by Starry.sg.</p>
      <p>In this privacy policy, we explain what personal information we collect, how we use and disclose that data, and your choices regarding our handling of your data. This privacy policy is incorporated into our terms of use and forms a part of it.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="privacy__section">
      <h2>Important Notice</h2>
      <p>Before using our products, services, or submitting any personal information to us, please carefully read this privacy policy and contact us if you have any questions. Your use of the services signifies that you agree to the practices described in this privacy policy. If you do not agree to this privacy policy, please do not access the website or use the services in any way.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="privacy__section">
      <h2>The Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>This notice applies to all information collected or submitted on the Slax Reader website and the Slax Reader applications and services for iPhone, iPad, Android, Kindle, and other devices and platforms, hereafter referred to as simply Slax Reader.</p>
      <p>Slax Reader occasionally needs to collect information for convenience, practicality, or technical requirements. This information includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your chosen username, which may be your email address or name. A username is technically required so you can log in from multiple computers and devices. We encourage you to use your email address to make "forgot password" functionality possible.</li>
        <li>The titles, metadata from pages which you save to Slax Reader from websites, our applications, third-party applications using the our API, and any other means.</li>
        <li>The HTML contents of the pages you save to Slax Reader when recognized as a known login-requiring site. This is technically required to generate the Text view and other indexing features for sites that require logins or accounts, such as some major newspaper publishers. When HTML is saved for a page, it is only used within your account and is not revealed via social or sharing features.</li>
        <li>We may also use "cookie" technology. Among other things, we may use cookies or other tracking technology for the purposes of helping you navigate between pages efficiently to spare you from having to re-enter that information each time you visit.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="privacy__section">
      <h2>How We Use Your Personal Information</h2>
      <p>We collect and process all your personal data in accordance with relevant data protection regulations, particularly the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). We may use the collected personal information for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Providing and managing access to our services</li>
        <li>Providing new features or new services</li>
        <li>Product optimization, performance optimization, and troubleshooting</li>
        <li>Responding to your inquiries, comments, feedback, or issues</li>
        <li>Sending administrative information</li>
        <li>Preventing fraud, criminal activity, or abuse of our services</li>
        <li>Compliance with legal regulations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="privacy__section">
      <h2>Sharing and Disclosure of Personal Information</h2>
      <p>We do not rent or sell your information in personally identifiable form to anyone for profit. However, we may share your personal information with:</p>

      <h3>Third-Party Vendors</h3>
      <p>We engage vendors to provide services on our behalf, such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Business analytics</li>
        <li>Customer service</li>
        <li>Marketing</li>
        <li>Distribution</li>
        <li>Payment processing</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Business Partners</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>We may share information with partners for joint service provisions</li>
        <li>We do not control the privacy practices of these third-party partners</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Legal and Business Requirements</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Compliance with legal requirements</li>
        <li>Business transfers during mergers, acquisitions, or restructuring</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="privacy__section">
      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>

      <h3>Service Commitment</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>We provide services with reasonable technology and prudence</li>
        <li>We may determine the maximum storage period of your data</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Service Termination</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>We will announce service termination at least 30 days in advance</li>
        <li>After the deadline, we can terminate the service and stop data download services</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Liability Limitations</h3>
      <p>We are not liable for service interruptions caused by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Government policy changes</li>
        <li>Natural disasters</li>
        <li>Wars</li>
        <li>Communication line interruptions</li>
        <li>Hacker attacks</li>
        <li>Computer virus intrusions</li>
        <li>System adjustments</li>
        <li>Network failures</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="privacy__section">
      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you encounter product issues, technical malfunctions, or security concerns, please contact our technical support at: <a href="mailto:hi@starry.com">hi@starry.com</a></p>
    </section>

    <p class="privacy__closing">By using our services, you agree to these terms.</p>
  </div>
</div>

